        'desc_en'    => 'Santa Maria della Cancellata is one of Lacedonia\'s oldest and most historically layered churches, standing on the remains of a Roman-era sanctuary dedicated to the goddess Isis. Its sacred continuity spans over two millennia. In the 2nd century AD the pagan temple became a Christian place of worship; rebuilt in the 19th century after a period of abandonment, it was restructured after the 1930 earthquake and entrusted to the Franciscans. The church holds a remarkable place in Lacedonia\'s spiritual life: in 1948, the effigy of the Madonna dell\'Addolorata kept inside wept for approximately ten days, drawing national press attention and thousands of faithful from across Italy. The church preserves early Christian mosaics, Latin inscriptions and sacred artworks that visitors can explore in detail through the MetaBorghi 3D virtual tour.',
